was a good topic

00:08:07.220 --> 00:08:09.560
to try to see what Gaia means.

00:08:09.560 --> 00:08:11.560
I mention that in a minute.

00:08:11.560 --> 00:08:14.850
Then there is also, since I'm
an historian and sociologists

00:08:14.850 --> 00:08:16.940
of science, an empirical study.

00:08:16.940 --> 00:08:19.630
I'm studying a set of
scientists in basically

00:08:19.630 --> 00:08:22.030
what could be
called geomorphology

00:08:22.030 --> 00:08:28.480
or geobiomorphology, which I
will talk about in a minute.

00:08:28.480 --> 00:08:32.850
But also, even though I would
have less time for that, trying

00:08:32.850 --> 00:08:37.470
to use art as a way to gain
some sort of sensitivity

00:08:37.470 --> 00:08:40.760
to the question given that
one other thing we lack

00:08:40.760 --> 00:08:43.000
to understand the
politics of the climate

00:08:43.000 --> 00:08:47.050
is also the equipment, the
sort of sensitivity equipment,

00:08:47.050 --> 00:08:50.000
which only art can provide.

00:08:50.000 --> 00:08:53.960
So one word on the
empirical part before I

00:08:53.960 --> 00:08:57.650
get to the more complicated
section of his lecture.

00:08:57.650 --> 00:09:01.530
I'm studying people who
are calling themselves

00:09:01.530 --> 00:09:04.840
critical zone
observatory network.

00:09:04.840 --> 00:09:08.600
It's a set of people, NSF
is financing some of them

00:09:08.600 --> 00:09:11.700
in the US, and there are
many in China and in Europe,

00:09:11.700 --> 00:09:16.810
who are trying basically to
equip watersheds most often

00:09:16.810 --> 00:09:19.400
with as much
equipment as possible

00:09:19.400 --> 00:09:22.220
to make sure that we
begin to understand what

00:09:22.220 --> 00:09:23.510
the critical zone is for them.

00:09:23.510 --> 00:09:27.450
It is the top of the canopy
to the deep rock behind, which

00:09:27.450 --> 00:09:32.060
is basically all of
life form and to try

00:09:32.060 --> 00:09:36.800
to gain some sort of precise
knowledge, which in fact, we

00:09:36.800 --> 00:09:38.810
discovered, and I
discovered studying them.

00:09:38.810 --> 00:09:41.930
We don't have about
complex reaction

00:09:41.930 --> 00:09:45.580
of weathering the soil, the
transformation of the soil,

00:09:45.580 --> 00:09:47.740
and all of the
other entities which

00:09:47.740 --> 00:09:51.610
are summarized very nicely
in this beautiful drawing

00:09:51.610 --> 00:09:53.230
by Paul Duvingeaud.

00:09:53.230 --> 00:09:56.140
And what I'm interested
in is especially

00:09:56.140 --> 00:09:59.800
to try to understand how these
different groups of scientists

00:09:59.800 --> 00:10:04.000
spread around the world build
what you could call feedback

00:10:04.000 --> 00:10:07.480
loops to make us the
science first, but then also

00:10:07.480 --> 00:10:10.280
the general public
around this watershed

00:10:10.280 --> 00:10:13.870
sensitive to the
effect of the action

00:10:13.870 --> 00:10:16.360
on the space in which we are.

00:10:16.360 --> 00:10:19.044
In fact, we realize, and I
realize [INAUDIBLE] scientists.

00:10:19.044 --> 00:10:20.460
But it's extremely
difficult to be

00:10:20.460 --> 00:10:23.280
sensitive to what
happened to the land,

00:10:23.280 --> 00:10:26.410
and to the territory,
and the soil we inhabit.

00:10:26.410 --> 00:10:28.850
So this is a nice example.

00:10:28.850 --> 00:10:31.950
This is one of the
observatories [INAUDIBLE]

00:10:31.950 --> 00:10:36.090
in the top of a
mountain in California.

00:10:36.090 --> 00:10:38.420
And there is almost
no connection

00:10:38.420 --> 00:10:41.040
strangely enough between
the observatory, which

00:10:41.040 --> 00:10:42.620
is on the top of the mountain.

00:10:42.620 --> 00:10:45.230
It is green and somewhat
wet, not this year,

00:10:45.230 --> 00:10:46.590
but it used to be wet.

00:10:46.590 --> 00:10:48.700
And then you have a
Central Valley completely

00:10:48.700 --> 00:10:52.100
flat, completely polluted,
a completely different

00:10:52.100 --> 00:10:55.610
environment where you have a
main agrobusiness of the United

00:10:55.610 --> 00:10:56.630
States, as you know.

00:10:56.630 --> 00:11:00.060
But the connection between the
two, the input in the Sierra

00:11:00.060 --> 00:11:02.920
and the output in the
water is so deficient

00:11:02.920 --> 00:11:07.580
that actually people pump their
fields out against one another

00:11:07.580 --> 00:11:10.020
until there would
be no water left,

00:11:10.020 --> 00:11:12.240
at least if a drought goes on.

00:11:12.240 --> 00:11:14.610
So I'm interested in a
way a group of scientists

00:11:14.610 --> 00:11:16.870
are trying to build
the instrumentation

00:11:16.870 --> 00:11:22.190
to render sensitive the
presence and the lack of water

00:11:22.190 --> 00:11:26.370
in the top with what the
scientists, and engineers,

00:11:26.370 --> 00:11:29.730
and agrobusinesses
do in the bottom.

00:11:29.730 --> 00:11:32.490
As you see in the bottom
left, bottom right, sorry,

00:11:32.490 --> 00:11:34.510
these are some of
the immense pumps,

00:11:34.510 --> 00:11:37.410
which actually have no meters,
which is an interesting case.

00:11:37.410 --> 00:11:39.320
There is no meter in California.

00:11:39.320 --> 00:11:42.260
So you can use as much
water as you wish.

00:11:42.260 --> 00:11:44.920
So the building of those
loops if you imagine

00:11:44.920 --> 00:11:48.380
the whole ignorance in which
we are about the reaction

00:11:48.380 --> 00:11:49.780
not only of the
Earth in general,

00:11:49.780 --> 00:11:53.100
but every one of
these set ups, is

00:11:53.100 --> 00:11:56.180
as if we had to build
some haptic device

00:11:56.180 --> 00:11:59.070
to render sensitive
to our action, which

00:11:59.070 --> 00:12:04.180
is of course the whole problem
of ecological in general.

00:12:04.180 --> 00:12:08.160
Now, what is interesting is that
the critical zone observatory

00:12:08.160 --> 00:12:11.250
can take a slightly
larger meaning.

00:12:11.250 --> 00:12:13.610
To mean and hear the
word critical in the sort

00:12:13.610 --> 00:12:16.480
of technical sense means
the fragile and far

00:12:16.480 --> 00:12:20.350
from equilibrium very
thin layers inside which

00:12:20.350 --> 00:12:22.710
everything in life exists.

00:12:22.710 --> 00:12:26.560
This is a quote
by Tim Lenton, one

00:12:26.560 --> 00:12:28.530
of the student of Jim Lovelock.

00:12:28.530 --> 00:12:30.820
"For many Earth
systems scientists,

00:12:30.820 --> 00:12:32.780
the planet Earth
is really comprised

00:12:32.780 --> 00:12:35.790
of two systems, the
surface system that

00:12:35.790 --> 00:12:40.370
supports life and the great bulk
of the inner Earth underneath.

00:12:40.370 --> 00:12:44.050
It is a thin layer of the system
at the surface of the Earth,

00:12:44.050 --> 00:12:46.310
and it's remarkable
property that

00:12:46.310 --> 00:12:49.370
is the subject of my work"
and the work of the Earth

00:12:49.370 --> 00:12:50.210
scientist.

00:12:50.210 --> 00:12:53.200
Now, this is quite
interesting to try to imagine

00:12:53.200 --> 00:12:55.230
how these thin layers exist.

00:12:55.230 --> 00:12:57.140
And I'm being
completely obsessed

00:12:57.140 --> 00:13:02.390
by the difference between the
vision we have of the group

00:13:02.390 --> 00:13:05.850
and the vision we have of
this thin layer when we follow

00:13:05.850 --> 00:13:10.760
the work of these
geoscientists and what

00:13:10.760 --> 00:13:13.070
those I call, somewhat
affectionately,

00:13:13.070 --> 00:13:14.850
critical zoneists.

00:13:14.850 --> 00:13:17.540
And this is actually
fairly difficult.

00:13:17.540 --> 00:13:20.610
This is why it's always
interesting to relate also

00:13:20.610 --> 00:13:23.910
to the artist, and this
is part of a project

00:13:23.910 --> 00:13:25.920
that I have with
geoscientist and artist

00:13:25.920 --> 00:13:29.920
to try to represent, to give a
feeling for what it is to think

00:13:29.920 --> 00:13:31.840
of the Earth as thin layers.

00:13:31.840 --> 00:13:35.410
They sometimes talk about the
skin given some of the varnish,

00:13:35.410 --> 00:13:37.490
not the whole
nature, but something

00:13:37.490 --> 00:13:41.230
which is much smaller, much
more fragile, and much thinner.

00:13:41.230 --> 00:13:44.970
And here the artist,
Alexandra Arenes

00:13:44.970 --> 00:13:48.490
tried to use cadmium
layers of trees

00:13:48.490 --> 00:13:50.590
were trying to imagine
what it could be.

00:13:50.590 --> 00:13:52.720
But it's, of course,
very difficult to think

00:13:52.720 --> 00:13:58.210
of these thin layers
in any sensible way.

00:13:58.210 --> 00:14:01.512
I cannot resist showing you
this little work of art by Sarah

00:14:01.512 --> 00:14:05.890
Sze, which I've seen
a week ago in New.

00:14:05.890 --> 00:14:08.610
York.

00:14:08.610 --> 00:14:12.780
It was an amazing piece
where there is precisely

00:14:12.780 --> 00:14:14.680
no clear geometry,
but you are still

00:14:14.680 --> 00:14:17.790
surrounded by the
multiplicity of entity which

00:14:17.790 --> 00:14:23.860
she has assembled to describe
as complex and difficult a way

00:14:23.860 --> 00:14:28.290
what it is to be in
this critical zone.

00:14:28.290 --> 00:14:31.240
But sorry, this
is my own camera.

00:14:31.240 --> 00:14:36.400
I'm trying to get a peek at this
work, which is not yet shown.

00:14:36.400 --> 00:14:38.940
And I propose to code it
since the work is still

00:14:38.940 --> 00:14:40.930
entitled critical
zone, because it's

00:14:40.930 --> 00:14:43.330
too beautiful to be not used.

00:14:43.330 --> 00:14:49.300
OK, so the reason why this
work by the geoscientists

00:14:49.300 --> 00:14:52.370
seemed to me so
interesting is because it

00:14:52.370 --> 00:14:56.140
reopened a sort of
critical leverage

00:14:56.140 --> 00:14:58.500
against the notion of a globe.

00:14:58.500 --> 00:15:00.770
The global is actually
something we immediately

00:15:00.770 --> 00:15:02.437
associate with the
ecological question,

00:15:02.437 --> 00:15:04.520
and it's killing us,
basically, because every time

00:15:04.520 --> 00:15:07.200
you have a global, and you have
to absorb the idea that it's

00:15:07.200 --> 00:15:08.870
a global phenomenon,
and people make

00:15:08.870 --> 00:15:10.650
these big gestures
with their hand,

00:15:10.650 --> 00:15:13.590
yes, OK, but that's the
size of a pumpkin, right?

00:15:13.590 --> 00:15:15.180
I mean it's not much bigger.

00:15:15.180 --> 00:15:18.200
And in fact, we are
always lost in this globe,

00:15:18.200 --> 00:15:20.280
and we don't know
how to handle it.

00:15:20.280 --> 00:15:21.880
So there's a very
clear sense in which

00:15:21.880 --> 00:15:24.830
we need to feel
something else and have

00:15:24.830 --> 00:15:29.480
another imagination or another
mythological imagination,

00:15:29.480 --> 00:15:32.540
and also scientific, to
try to capture something

00:15:32.540 --> 00:15:36.121
which has been criticized
so excellently by Peter

00:15:36.121 --> 00:15:36.620
Sloterdijk.

00:15:36.620 --> 00:15:39.400
Of course, in the Whole Earth
Catalog, which is now many,

00:15:39.400 --> 00:15:41.810
many years ago, we were
supposed to be all unified

00:15:41.810 --> 00:15:43.880
by this notion of a
blue planet, right?

00:15:43.880 --> 00:15:45.050
The image of a blue planet.

00:15:45.050 --> 00:15:49.660
Every book about ecology
says since the blue planet,

00:15:49.660 --> 00:15:52.640
we know we are in the same
place, and we are all united.

00:15:52.640 --> 00:15:55.360
And politics is now a
sort of unanimous activity

00:15:55.360 --> 00:15:56.590
as we all know.

00:15:56.590 --> 00:15:58.460
And it has been a
complete failure.

00:15:58.460 --> 00:16:01.240
The more we get into
ecological questions,

00:16:01.240 --> 00:16:03.960
the more dispute and
strife increases.

00:16:03.960 --> 00:16:06.270
So the idea that we
are united by the globe

00:16:06.270 --> 00:16:08.650
is actually a misreading
of the blue planet.

00:16:08.650 --> 00:16:11.120
And of course, the image
is also a misreading

00:16:11.120 --> 00:16:14.310
of the blue planet conceived
as a critical zone,

00:16:14.310 --> 00:16:17.320
because it sees far apart
and from the outside,

00:16:17.320 --> 00:16:21.260
and we are inside the layers,
and we see it laterally,

00:16:21.260 --> 00:16:22.190
so to speak.

00:16:22.190 --> 00:16:25.210
So there is nothing
more wrong, in a way,

00:16:25.210 --> 00:16:26.570
than the image of a blue planet.

00:16:26.570 --> 00:16:30.300
And it's also associated, as
Peter Sloterdijk has shown

00:16:30.300 --> 00:16:33.830
in the second volume of his
work on the globe, [INAUDIBLE],

00:16:33.830 --> 00:16:35.680
sorry, that's the
second tome, me

00:16:35.680 --> 00:16:38.210
is called Globe with
too many globes.

00:16:38.210 --> 00:16:39.720
There is the Roman Empire.

00:16:39.720 --> 00:16:42.970
There are large numbers of
religious images associating

00:16:42.970 --> 00:16:47.620
the [INAUDIBLE] with the
power and the domination

00:16:47.620 --> 00:16:49.550
of a Christian God.

00:16:49.550 --> 00:16:52.030
And of course, there
are many other types

00:16:52.030 --> 00:16:54.860
of globes which are
layered on top of this one.

00:16:54.860 --> 00:16:56.970
So whenever we have
the globe as a sort

00:16:56.970 --> 00:17:04.579
of very powerful metaphor, we
are sort of squashed, as Atlas

00:17:04.579 --> 00:17:08.050
and literally
flattened by the weight

00:17:08.050 --> 00:17:10.980
of this huge globe, which
is supposed to be taken out.

00:17:10.980 --> 00:17:12.530
Even with the notion
of Anthropocene

00:17:12.530 --> 00:17:14.900
the dean mentioned,
that's precisely

00:17:14.900 --> 00:17:17.410
from the agent of
history able to live

00:17:17.410 --> 00:17:20.119
at the time of the Anthropocene
does not really exist.

00:17:20.119 --> 00:17:24.079
It's not a [INAUDIBLE],
all of little human

00:17:24.079 --> 00:17:27.369
that were here in this
room and 8 billion others.

00:17:27.369 --> 00:17:31.120
So there is a real problem
of, how could I say,

00:17:31.120 --> 00:17:33.050
imaginary metaphysic,
if you want,

00:17:33.050 --> 00:17:37.110
how to describe
agency at the time

00:17:37.110 --> 00:17:41.400
so that the globe doesn't
crush us, so to speak.

00:17:41.400 --> 00:17:43.580
And there's another
question with global,

00:17:43.580 --> 00:17:45.560
which I find extremely
disturbing is

00:17:45.560 --> 00:17:48.540
that globalization-- the
word global in globalization

00:17:48.540 --> 00:17:51.820
means to entirely
different elements.

00:17:51.820 --> 00:17:54.060
One of them is,
of course, a sort

00:17:54.060 --> 00:17:57.150
of very classic, very
traditional, and in a way,

00:17:57.150 --> 00:17:59.980
quite beautiful cartographic
principle, which

00:17:59.980 --> 00:18:05.110
registers with a very simple
principle of longitude

00:18:05.110 --> 00:18:07.000
and latitude, as
many differences as

00:18:07.000 --> 00:18:09.920
possible, as the whole of
geography has been able to do.

00:18:09.920 --> 00:18:11.140
It's map differences.

00:18:11.140 --> 00:18:13.880
And the more differences
are multiplied

00:18:13.880 --> 00:18:18.360
even because they are registered
with a very simple idiom.

00:18:18.360 --> 00:18:21.500
But globalization also means
exactly the opposite, which

00:18:21.500 --> 00:18:25.630
is the extension of the very
tiny provincial small numbers

00:18:25.630 --> 00:18:30.750
of settled cliches, so to speak,
extended to the whole planet.

00:18:30.750 --> 00:18:33.590
So you never know when people
are against globalization,

00:18:33.590 --> 00:18:36.550
if they are against the
globalization conceived

00:18:36.550 --> 00:18:38.875
according to the
cartographic globe,

00:18:38.875 --> 00:18:41.420
or if they are actually doing
something entirely different,

00:18:41.420 --> 00:18:44.070
which is resisting,
maybe some good reason,

00:18:44.070 --> 00:18:47.780
the extension of the
cliched, standardized, very

00:18:47.780 --> 00:18:50.850
simple provincial definition
of what it is a human, how

00:18:50.850 --> 00:18:53.950
to calculate selfishness,
for instance, self-interest,

00:18:53.950 --> 00:18:59.050
and how to establish the
calculation of a common life,

00:18:59.050 --> 00:19:02.160
which means that actually
one of the questions

00:19:02.160 --> 00:19:06.680
why the notion of globalization
is so diverse, if you want,

00:19:06.680 --> 00:19:09.790
when we are right now
in the press always

00:19:09.790 --> 00:19:12.670
talking about people who
are voting strangely,

00:19:12.670 --> 00:19:16.640
because they are left down or
left over by globalization.

00:19:16.640 --> 00:19:17.740
Which one?

00:19:17.740 --> 00:19:20.480
Is globalization an extension
of the numbers of difference

00:19:20.480 --> 00:19:23.470
which register or
simplification and, in a way,

00:19:23.470 --> 00:19:25.990
an impoverishment
of a difference.

00:19:25.990 --> 00:19:27.720
And I think it's
a serious point.

00:19:27.720 --> 00:19:30.540
But the second difficulty
with the global

00:19:30.540 --> 00:19:33.450
is of course to understand
the life forms, which

00:19:33.450 --> 00:19:37.275
are themselves composing this
very thin critical zone with,

00:19:37.275 --> 00:19:40.960
as we know, from Jim Lovelock's
work and many others of system

00:19:40.960 --> 00:19:43.960
scientists is actually
resisted and made

00:19:43.960 --> 00:19:47.870
to be a critical zone by the
exchangers and overlapping

00:19:47.870 --> 00:19:52.760
of all the entities, which are
composing the life form-- which

00:19:52.760 --> 00:19:55.310
are composing the
critical zone, sorry.

00:19:55.310 --> 00:20:00.300
So this is what I call the Gaia
problem, which of course, Gaia

00:20:00.300 --> 00:20:03.950
is a very complex
set of metaphors.

00:20:03.950 --> 00:20:07.650
It's difficult
and old mythology.

00:20:07.650 --> 00:20:09.130
And it's not sure
that Lovelock was

00:20:09.130 --> 00:20:12.150
right in using this
old mythological term.

00:20:12.150 --> 00:20:15.000
But I think it's
very interesting

00:20:15.000 --> 00:20:19.770
to have precisely in
the hands of Lovelock,

00:20:19.770 --> 00:20:24.240
speaking of early Lovelock,
because now, he is a bit old.

00:20:24.240 --> 00:20:29.730
We will all be at the end-- not
to say senile, to be polite.

00:20:29.730 --> 00:20:33.440
But what is interesting is that
precisely a mythical figure,

00:20:33.440 --> 00:20:37.850
and a scientific figure, and
a disputed figure, and also

00:20:37.850 --> 00:20:41.430
a source of strange
religious cults as well.

00:20:41.430 --> 00:20:43.501
I'm not that much
interested in the cult part,

00:20:43.501 --> 00:20:45.750
but I'm very interested in
the link between metallurgy

00:20:45.750 --> 00:20:47.520
and science, because
exactly what we need,

00:20:47.520 --> 00:20:51.080
which is a sort of set of
concepts which allows us

00:20:51.080 --> 00:20:55.430
to gain the grasp on the
non-global and yet overlapping

00:20:55.430 --> 00:20:58.000
and connected set
of entities that

00:20:58.000 --> 00:21:04.410
is a great innovation for
me of Lovelock and friends

00:21:04.410 --> 00:21:07.340
and very important
contributor Lynn Margulis.

00:21:07.340 --> 00:21:11.890
And I wrote a paper
in Culture and Society

00:21:11.890 --> 00:21:14.630
against, to give you an idea
of the difficulty of what

00:21:14.630 --> 00:21:19.450
I call the Gaia problem,
of a book by a Earth system

00:21:19.450 --> 00:21:24.400
scientist called
Toby Tyrrell, who

00:21:24.400 --> 00:21:29.410
makes a scientific critique
of Gaia, of Lovelock,

00:21:29.410 --> 00:21:34.990
by using precisely a globalist
model of what the Earth is

00:21:34.990 --> 00:21:35.860
like.

00:21:35.860 --> 00:21:37.545
And it's a small
technical point,

00:21:37.545 --> 00:21:38.920
but I think it's
important to see

00:21:38.920 --> 00:21:42.220
the extent of which
the notion of globe

00:21:42.220 --> 00:21:46.410
makes us unable to have
the political agency

00:21:46.410 --> 00:21:49.280
necessary to handle the
ecological crisis, a very

00:21:49.280 --> 00:21:51.540
small, but very
interesting example.

00:21:51.540 --> 00:21:55.240
So Tyrrell is actually
reusing in his book,

00:21:55.240 --> 00:22:00.290
Against Lovelock, a completely
traditional metaphor, which has

00:22:00.290 --> 00:22:01.950
nothing scientific about it.

00:22:01.950 --> 00:22:07.070
It's as old as the fable of the
members [INAUDIBLE] of which

00:22:07.070 --> 00:22:08.680
there are many versions.

00:22:08.680 --> 00:22:12.520
And he says when
Lovelock talks about Gaia

00:22:12.520 --> 00:22:16.780
is actually supposing that
there is a super organism, which

00:22:16.780 --> 00:22:20.710
is called Gaia, which as a
sort of providential character

00:22:20.710 --> 00:22:25.250
and is governing the
life forms under it.

00:22:25.250 --> 00:22:28.400
And the whole strangeness
of the argument

00:22:28.400 --> 00:22:31.710
is that it's actually a
fable from political science

00:22:31.710 --> 00:22:33.820
and political scientists
know it very well,

00:22:33.820 --> 00:22:37.170
imported into Earth system
science to criticize,

00:22:37.170 --> 00:22:40.370
in this case, Lovelock,
which never said that.

00:22:40.370 --> 00:22:42.490
So it's a series of
misunderstandings,

00:22:42.490 --> 00:22:44.780
which I find extremely
enlightening,

00:22:44.780 --> 00:22:48.080
because it comes precisely for
someone who says I'm giving

00:22:48.080 --> 00:22:51.090
a scientific critique
of a mythical argument,

00:22:51.090 --> 00:22:52.640
which has been
made by Lovelock ,

00:22:52.640 --> 00:22:55.630
as if Lovelock had actually
imagined that there was life

00:22:55.630 --> 00:23:00.814
and that life was actually
leading the life forms,

00:23:00.814 --> 00:23:02.980
which is, of course, often
associated with his name,

00:23:02.980 --> 00:23:03.938
but he never said that.

00:23:03.938 --> 00:23:05.660
Let me read just two
quotes. "Lovelock

00:23:05.660 --> 00:23:08.670
suggests that life has
had a hand on the tiller

00:23:08.670 --> 00:23:10.250
of environmental control."

00:23:10.250 --> 00:23:12.750
I love his expression
of a tiller, which

00:23:12.750 --> 00:23:16.590
is of course literally
a cybernetics metaphor

00:23:16.590 --> 00:23:20.010
and which proposes that there is
super order, which is actually

00:23:20.010 --> 00:23:23.810
adjusting, like a
thermostat, the life form.

00:23:23.810 --> 00:23:27.200
"And intervention of life in
the regulation of the planet

00:23:27.200 --> 00:23:31.220
has been such as to promote
stability and keep condition

00:23:31.220 --> 00:23:34.340
favorable to life," which
is quite extraordinary,

00:23:34.340 --> 00:23:38.570
as if you had something further
on top of all the overlapping

00:23:38.570 --> 00:23:42.370
entity, which could
super state, if you want,

00:23:42.370 --> 00:23:46.380
with a state metaphor, imposed
by biologists or Earth systems

00:23:46.380 --> 00:23:49.510
scientists, to criticize
someone who never said that.

00:23:49.510 --> 00:23:51.430
"A well-regulated
planet could hardly

00:23:51.430 --> 00:23:54.330
be blamed for being buffeted
about by the vagaries

00:23:54.330 --> 00:23:56.550
of celestial mechanics
and collision

00:23:56.550 --> 00:24:00.110
and can even be congratulated
for its multiple recoveries

00:24:00.110 --> 00:24:03.169
from the terrible devastation
of extraterrestrial impact."

00:24:03.169 --> 00:24:04.960
And here you see that
the figure of a state

00:24:04.960 --> 00:24:08.940
is actually a divine figure
coming straight from religion.

00:24:08.940 --> 00:24:10.910
That's why it's always
complicated to talk

00:24:10.910 --> 00:24:13.160
about the science of
ecology, because you never

00:24:13.160 --> 00:24:15.780
know if you're talking about
science, theology, politics,

00:24:15.780 --> 00:24:18.580
and if it's not the metaphor
of a state, which is actually

00:24:18.580 --> 00:24:22.410
sneaked in everywhere when we do
have a pumpkin jesters of let's

00:24:22.410 --> 00:24:23.740
think globally.

00:24:23.740 --> 00:24:27.400
So this is why we have to be
careful of pumpkins in general.

00:24:30.340 --> 00:24:33.296
Philosophically, and I'm
also interested in this part,

00:24:33.296 --> 00:24:36.330
of course, in my own
work on actual network

00:24:36.330 --> 00:24:40.480
theory is that the very
notion that ecology is made

00:24:40.480 --> 00:24:42.820
of parts and a whole,
which has been,

00:24:42.820 --> 00:24:47.240
of course, a bane of
the notion of ecosystem,

00:24:47.240 --> 00:24:50.637
is actually something which
is largely an artifact,

00:24:50.637 --> 00:24:52.470
I mean, in the literal
sense of an artifact.

00:24:52.470 --> 00:24:54.760
It's actually a
technical metaphor,

00:24:54.760 --> 00:24:58.180
which is used to understand
biological forms.

00:24:58.180 --> 00:25:01.750
But biological forms are
not made of parts and whole.

00:25:01.750 --> 00:25:04.260
They are actually
overlapping entities.

00:25:04.260 --> 00:25:06.330
And those overlapping
entities are actually

00:25:06.330 --> 00:25:08.347
not well understood if
you say it was part,

00:25:08.347 --> 00:25:09.930
and then you have
all the little part,

00:25:09.930 --> 00:25:12.460
and then you have something
which is not in any of a part,

00:25:12.460 --> 00:25:15.660
but of which is superior to
all of them, a sort of plan,

00:25:15.660 --> 00:25:20.300
and we are about 1 centimeter
from a divine intervention

00:25:20.300 --> 00:25:20.990
here.

00:25:20.990 --> 00:25:22.970
And again, it's an
artist who's very

00:25:22.970 --> 00:25:26.790
good at showing that, Damian
Ortega, because he showed

00:25:26.790 --> 00:25:30.666
in an ironic way that, in
fact, even for cars, it

00:25:30.666 --> 00:25:33.120
is a Volkswagen
Beetle, even for cars,

00:25:33.120 --> 00:25:36.180
you never have actually
part and whole.

00:25:36.180 --> 00:25:38.420
I had the pleasure of
writing a whole book

00:25:38.420 --> 00:25:41.470
on a subway, automated
subway on his question,

00:25:41.470 --> 00:25:43.220
because the very
way in which you

00:25:43.220 --> 00:25:45.890
invent if you are an
engineer and invent

00:25:45.890 --> 00:25:47.770
a highly complex
technical process

00:25:47.770 --> 00:25:50.110
is you actually
always need to have

00:25:50.110 --> 00:25:52.980
the interconnection and the
overlapping of the parts.

00:25:52.980 --> 00:25:55.150
It's only when the
technology is actually

00:25:55.150 --> 00:25:57.900
ready to be discarded
that you can extract

00:25:57.900 --> 00:26:01.010
the part from the
activity of the engineers

00:26:01.010 --> 00:26:03.720
as Simondon has so well shown.

00:26:03.720 --> 00:26:07.960
So the key question is
that of overlapping entity.

00:26:07.960 --> 00:26:11.970
If we take the
Margulis-Lovelock seriously,

00:26:11.970 --> 00:26:14.680
we have a very different
view of the parts and whole.

00:26:14.680 --> 00:26:18.080
We have entirely
selfish entities,

00:26:18.080 --> 00:26:22.380
except they cannot decide
where the limit of the self is

00:26:22.380 --> 00:26:25.740
and that the key invention of
Margulis at the small scale,

00:26:25.740 --> 00:26:29.010
as you know, and
Lovelock the large scale,

00:26:29.010 --> 00:26:32.440
which is that very definition
of a boundary of a self is

00:26:32.440 --> 00:26:34.630
precisely [INAUDIBLE]
of life forms,

00:26:34.630 --> 00:26:38.120
including boundaries of
a critical zone itself.

00:26:38.120 --> 00:26:41.570
So if that begins to give
you a handle of the question

00:26:41.570 --> 00:26:45.670
I was interested in,
of the notion of globe.

00:26:45.670 --> 00:26:48.550
And this is actually a
very interesting paper

00:26:48.550 --> 00:26:51.770
by Scott Gilbert, who took
a title of one of my book,

00:26:51.770 --> 00:26:55.600
but differently, and who wrote
a symbiotic view of life.

00:26:55.600 --> 00:26:58.230
We have never been
individuals and introduced

00:26:58.230 --> 00:27:01.330
the notion of holobiont,
which is taking up

00:27:01.330 --> 00:27:03.720
some part of biology
right now that always

00:27:03.720 --> 00:27:05.900
with the same
question, if we are not

00:27:05.900 --> 00:27:09.730
part and whole, but overlapping
entity, what becomes

00:27:09.730 --> 00:27:12.020
of the great question
of sovereignty,

00:27:12.020 --> 00:27:16.490
which has been imported from
political science and mythology

00:27:16.490 --> 00:27:21.040
inside biology and which is
now resisted by biologists

00:27:21.040 --> 00:27:23.116
like Gilbert and many
others to say, no, no, no,

00:27:23.116 --> 00:27:24.490
parts and whole
has nothing to do

00:27:24.490 --> 00:27:28.710
with the way life
forms actually develop.

00:27:28.710 --> 00:27:32.590
And that's where the question
of sovereignty at all scales

00:27:32.590 --> 00:27:37.080
and for all entities began to
be really interesting for me.

00:27:37.080 --> 00:27:38.850
And that's where
I was completely

00:27:38.850 --> 00:27:42.880
stupefied reading the article
of Nature, the first time when

00:27:42.880 --> 00:27:47.430
Nature is actually talking about
the notion of Anthropocene,

